# Customer Service Chatbot

## Overview
This project is a comprehensive Customer Service Chatbot designed to assist users by answering queries, providing relevant information from a knowledge base, and offering personalized support through natural language processing techniques. The chatbot integrates multiple AI-powered modules including sentiment analysis, intent classification, named entity recognition, and knowledge retrieval to deliver an efficient and interactive user experience.

## Features
- **Sentiment Analysis:** Detects the emotional tone of user messages to tailor responses accordingly.
- **Intent Classification:** Understands user intentions to route queries correctly.
- **Named Entity Recognition (NER):** Extracts important entities such as dates, locations, and product names from text.
- **Knowledge Base Retrieval:** Searches and retrieves relevant answers from a curated knowledge base using similarity matching.
- **FAQ Matching:** Provides quick answers to frequently asked questions via rule-based matching.
- **Chatbot Response Generation:** Generates contextual responses based on user input and recognized intents.
- **User Feedback Analysis:** Collects and processes user feedback to improve chatbot performance.
- **Topic Modeling:** Identifies main topics in conversations for better understanding and analytics.
- **Chat History Logging:** Stores conversation history for audit and improvement purposes.

## Technologies Used
- Python 3.x
- [TextBlob](https://textblob.readthedocs.io/en/dev/) for Sentiment Analysis
- [spaCy](https://spacy.io/) for Named Entity Recognition
- [scikit-learn](https://scikit-learn.org/) for Intent Classification and Knowledge Retrieval
- [gensim](https://radimrehurek.com/gensim/) for Topic Modeling
- JSON for chat logging and data storage

